mon_api.py
================

Description
-----------
POC of DOTM Monitoring API

Installing requirements
-----------------------
$ pip3 install -r requirements.txt
Or install packages with modules listed in requirements.txt provided by your OS package manager.

Configuring
-----------
Create file .mr.developer.cfg:
[monitoring]
url =  https://mon.example.com
user = monuser
paswd = monpaswd
hosts_key = dotm::mon::hosts
services_key = dotm::mon::services
config_key = dotm::mon::config
config_key_prefix = %(config_key)s::

[redis]
host = 127.0.0.1
port = 6379

Running
-------
$ python3 mon_api.py

Testing
-------
$ curl -i http://localhost:8081/mon/hosts/uk-www2
$ curl -i http://localhost:8081/mon/hosts/uk-www2/status
$ curl -i http://localhost:8081/mon/services/uk-www2
$ curl -i http://localhost:8081/mon/hosts/404
$ curl -X POST -i http://localhost:8081/mon/reload

